# Git Conventions

## Commit Message Format

```
type(scope): subject

body (detailed description)
```

### Types

- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `refactor`: Code refactoring (no functional change)
- `docs`: Documentation only
- `test`: Adding or updating tests
- `chore`: Build, CI, or tooling changes
- `perf`: Performance improvements

### Scope (Module Names)

- `admin`: xxl-job-admin module
- `core`: xxl-job-core module
- `executor`: Executor samples or Python executor
- `rpc`: RPC/communication layer
- `scheduler`: Scheduling logic
- `docker`: Docker/deployment configs

### Subject

- Use English, imperative mood ("add" not "added")
- No period at end
- Max 50 characters

### Body (Required for non-trivial changes)

- Explain WHAT changed and WHY
- Reference related issues if applicable
- Describe breaking changes if any

## Example

```
feat(scheduler): add support for streaming task callbacks

- Implement StreamingCallbackHandler for chunked data reporting
- Add new endpoint /api/streamCallback in OpenApiController
- Update TriggerCallbackThread to handle streaming mode

This enables Python executors to report partial results during
long-running data collection tasks instead of waiting until completion.

Closes #123
```
